Iavan Pijoos, News24(Supplied: Netcare911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; An 8-year-old disabled girl drowned while bathing at her home in the Johannesburg CBD on Monday morning, paramedics said.Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said the girl was assessed for signs of life by a Netcare 911 emergency care practitioner, but showed none.She was declared dead on the scene.It was not immediately clear where the girl's parents were, or what the nature of her disability was.Police are investigating the incident.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.